There is a known problem with plugins using bandana: when upgrading plugins, a ClassCastException is thrown whenever try to retrieve a value that was put on the cache prior to upgrading the plugin. See comments on See Comments in http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Persistence+in+Confluence

Because of this, Bandana can only be (safely) used in plugins with basic classes (i.e. String) :-(

A compromise would be to allow for flushing the values from the cache. This way, it is possible to work around the issue.

It'd looks like this:
{code}
MyConfigClass config;
try {
    config = bandanaManager.getValue(context,"MY_KEY");
} catch (ClassCastException e) {
    bandanaManager.flushValue("MY_KEY");
    config = bandanaManager.getValue(context,"MY_KEY");
}
{code}

